			<common:generalComment xml:lang="en">Plastic waste refers to the discarded materials made of plastic that accumulate in the environment. Plastics are a significant part of municipal solid waste, with containers and packaging being the largest contributors. In 2018, over 14.5 million tons of plastic waste were generated from packaging alone. Recycling of plastic waste involves the recovery and transformation of plastic materials to create new products, reducing the need for virgin raw materials and helping to protect the environment from pollution and greenhouse gas emissions. Despite the benefits, recycling rates for plastics are lower compared to materials like aluminum, glass, and paper.</common:generalComment>
			<common:generalComment xml:lang="zh">塑料垃圾是指在环境中堆积的塑料废弃材料。塑料是城市固体废物的重要组成部分，其中容器和包装是最大的贡献者。2018 年，仅包装就产生了超过 1450 万吨的塑料垃圾。塑料垃圾的回收利用包括回收和转化塑料材料以制造新产品，从而减少对原始原材料的需求，并有助于保护环境免受污染和温室气体排放。尽管好处多多，但与铝、玻璃和纸张等材料相比，塑料的回收率较低。</common:generalComment>
